### Database Setup Instructions -
### 1. Open PgAdmin
### 2. Within the Object Explorer view, navigate to Servers -> PostgreSQL [version] -> Databases
### 3. Right-click Databases and select Create -> Database
### 4. Name your database
### 5. Click Save
### Note: While you can setup and initialize the students table within Pgadmin's Query Tool (using the DDL.sql
### script in this repo, main.py takes care of this as well)

### Application Setup Instructions -
### 1. Install psycopg2 if not already installed using the command 'pip install psycopg2'
### 2. Open main.py and modify the parameters as needed that will be used for connecting to the database
###    - The variables can be found on lines 4 - 8
###    - Parameters: dbname, user, password, host, port
### 3. Run the program by executing main.py using the command 'python3 main.py'
### 4. The program will first establish a connection to the specified database, then create and initialize a students table with the corresponding initial data from the assignment specification
### 5. You will then be prompted with several options to choose from to interact with the database
###    - These options correspond to the CRUD operations as defined in the assignment specification
###        - i.e. getAllStudents(), addStudent(), updateStudentEmail(), deleteStudent()